
---


@startuml

' -----------------------------
' STEP 1 - Basic System Entities
' -----------------------------

class Customer {
    +String name
    +String address
    +String vatNumber
}

class Product {
    +String name
    +String description
    +int stockLevel
}

class Order {
    +int orderId
    +Date orderDate
    +boolean isPaid
    +boolean isShipped
}

class OrderLine {
    +int lineNumber
    +Product product
    +int quantity
}

class Delivery {
    +int deliveryId
    +Date shippedDate
    +Date receivedDate
    +String status
}

class Invoice {
    +int invoiceId
    +Date issuedDate
    +boolean isPaid
}

' Associations for STEP 1
Customer "1" --> "0..*" Order
Order "1" --> "1..*" OrderLine
OrderLine "1" --> "1" Product
Order "1" --> "1" Delivery
Order "1" --> "1" Invoice

' -----------------------------
' STEP 2 - Partial Shipments
' -----------------------------

class ShipmentGroup {
    +int groupId
    +List<OrderLine> linesInGroup
    +Date shippedDate
    +String status
}

OrderLine "1" --> "0..1" ShipmentGroup
ShipmentGroup "1" --> "1" Delivery

' -----------------------------
' STEP 3 - Multi-Warehouse & Invoicing
' -----------------------------

Customer {
    +String headOfficeAddress
    +List<String> warehouseAddresses
}

Order {
    +String deliveryAddress
}

Invoice {
    +String customerReference
    +float totalAmount
    +PaymentMethod paymentMethod
}

enum PaymentMethod {
    PAY_ON_DELIVERY
    PAY_UPFRONT
}

' -----------------------------
' STEP 4 - Enhanced Deliveries & Shipment Tracking
' -----------------------------

class Shipment {
    +int shipmentId
    +List<ShipmentGroup> groups
    +Date packedDate
    +Date shippedDate
    +Date receivedDate
    +String status
}

Delivery "1" --> "1" Shipment
ShipmentGroup "1" --> "1" Shipment

enum ShipmentStatus {
    PACKED
    SHIPPED
    DELIVERED
    LOST
    DAMAGED
}

@enduml

---

### 📌 **Explanation of Key Elements in the Diagram:**

- **`Customer`** now has multiple addresses (head office and warehouses).
- **`OrderLine`** can be grouped into **`ShipmentGroup`**, which tracks when it was shipped.
- **`ShipmentGroup`** is linked to **`Shipment`**, which handles tracking (packed, shipped, delivered, etc.).
- **`Delivery`** is replaced or extended by **`Shipment`**, which provides more detailed tracking capabilities.
- **`Invoice`** is added with options for **`PAY_ON_DELIVERY`** or **`PAY_UPFRONT`**.
- **`ShipmentStatus`** is an enumerated type to track the state of each shipment.

